... WAEC Examinations Commences on August 4 The Presidential Task Force (PTF) on COVID-19 says the recent rise of positive cases of the virus among people in positions of authority is a threat to governance and security.  Secretary to the Government of the Federation (SGF) and Chairman of the PTF, Mr Boss Mustapha, who made the observation during the task force media briefing in Abuja, however charged all Nigerians to be vigilant. The Minister of Aviation, Senator Hadi Sirika, says that the Nnamdi Azikiwe International Airport, Abuja, Murtala Muhammed International Airport, Lagos and Mallam Aminu Kano International Airport, Kano are ready for recommencement of domestic flights.  Our correspondent Nathan Williams reports that during the briefing, the Minister of State for Education, Emeka Nwajiuba, announced that the West African Senior School Certificate Examination (WASSCE) has been scheduled to commence on August 4th. 